This paper discusses the problem of inverse reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on comparing different algorithms for estimating the reward function in IRL, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
